<statement>
<p>
A population of bacteria is growing according to the equation <m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1000}{e}^{{{0.22}{t}}}</m>.  Estimate when the population will exceed 1935.</p>
<p>
<em>t</em>= <fillin characters="20" /> Â  </p>
<p>
Give your answer accurate to one decimal place.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>3.0004878476443</li></ul></p><p><m>\displaystyle{P}{\left({t}\right)}={1000}{e}^{{{0.22}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{1935}={1000}{e}^{{{0.22}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{1935}}{{1000}}={e}^{{{0.22}{t}}}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{\ln{{\left(\frac{{1935}}{{1000}}\right)}}}={0.22}{t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle\frac{{\ln{{\left(\frac{{1935}}{{1000}}\right)}}}}{{0.22}}={t}</m></p>
<p>
<m>\displaystyle{t}={3.0004878476443}</m></p>
</solution>
